WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.300
Leaving Windows behind? Your Edge can come with you. The live EdgeHub dashboard moves between System, Focus, and Glance screens.

00:06.300 --> 00:10.100
The front-facing display turns smoothly from landscape to portrait while the real Hub reflows.

00:10.100 --> 00:13.200
The camera pulls back from the portrait Hub to reveal EdgeHub Manager showing the matching portrait preview on a separate desktop monitor.

00:13.200 --> 00:18.400
Manager changes the orientation to landscape. The Hub turns smoothly and Manager returns to the matching landscape preview.

00:18.400 --> 00:27.400
Selecting screens in Manager changes the screen shown on the Hub.

00:27.400 --> 00:33.400
Manager adds a new screen. The Hub immediately opens the empty screen.

00:33.400 --> 00:39.400
Manager adds a CPU widget and changes the screen to two columns. Both changes appear live.

00:39.400 --> 00:46.400
Manager opens Look and selects the Aurora Edge theme.

00:46.400 --> 00:56.400
The Manager switches to dark mode, then a purple accent appears on both the preview and Hub.

00:56.400 --> 01:01.700
Device settings show the fixed landscape orientation and automatic update preference.

01:01.700 --> 01:05.900
Your favorite features. Your chosen OS. Custom development, built around the way you work.

01:05.900 --> 01:10.700
Build your Edge with EdgeHub for Linux. Tested on CachyOS, based on Arch Linux, with KDE Plasma on Wayland.
